I understand the issue you're experiencing. Since the food objects are moved far away from the center of the TrainingArea using local coordinates, their actual position in the world space might still interfere with other agents. To fix this, you can move the food objects out of reach specifically in the transform hierarchy of their respective TrainingArea.

Modify the `EatFood()` function in the `TrainingArea` script as follows:

```csharp
public void EatFood(GameObject food)
{
    // Move the food object far away and parent it to the TrainingArea.
    food.transform.parent = transform;
    food.transform.localPosition = Vector3.one * 9999;
}
```

This change will ensure that the food objects are moved out of reach within the local space of their TrainingArea in the transform hierarchy, and other agents should not be able to eat food from their respective TrainingArea.

If this method is still having issues, another approach is to use a boolean flag to check if the food object is eaten in the PlayerAgent script.

